# Vendor verification form ‚Äî SMS follow-up

## Rule

When a vendor **submits the verification form**, Ulo always texts them on the invite SMS thread:

1. **Acknowledgement** ‚Äî form received, under review.
2. **Status follow-up**
   - **Complete / verified** ‚Üí approved; eligible for work orders.
   - **Incomplete / needs review** ‚Üí list outstanding required items in plain language and ask them to finish / upload missing documents via the same `/v/:token` form link.

## Copy standards

- Follow `.cursor/rules/ulo-communication-writing-standard.mdc`.
- No internal jargon (no ‚Äúchecklist‚Äù, ‚Äúneeds_review‚Äù, IDs).
- Incomplete SMS: short bullets of outstanding item labels + form link on its own line.

## Implementation

- Helper: `supabase/functions/_shared/sms/vendorVerificationFollowUp.ts`
  - `buildVendorVerificationReceivedSms`
  - `buildVendorVerificationApprovedSms`
  - `buildVendorVerificationIncompleteSms` + `outstandingVerificationLabels`
  - `sendVendorVerificationFollowUpSms` (best-effort after submit)
- Triggered from `vendor-verification` Edge Function on successful form finalize/submit, after the inbox inbound mirror.
- Messages are real outbound SMS on the invite conversation (also visible in Communication).
- Graph events: `vendor.verification_ack_sent`, `vendor.verification_status_sent`, `vendor.verification_incomplete_followup_sent`.

## Do not

- Skip the acknowledgement when the form is already verified.
- Send incomplete follow-ups without naming what‚Äôs missing or without the form link.
- Rely only on in-app/admin UI ‚Äî the vendor must hear status over SMS.
